M_END--> - A powerful charting and visualization library for browser.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-06T03:05:43.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free and Open Source Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://c3js.org/\">C3.js</a> - D3 based reusable chart library.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-05T06:09:49.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free and Open Source Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/plotly/plotly.js\">Plotly</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/plotly/plotly.js\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">15k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":15045,\"repo\":\"plotly/plotly.js\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Built on top of d3 and stack.gl, allowing users to create basic charts and SVG maps.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-05T06:09:49.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free and Open Source Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jacomyal/sigma.js\">sigma.js</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jacomyal/sigma.js\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">10.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":10171,\"repo\":\"jacomyal/sigma.js\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Graphs / Network diagram library built with canvas.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-02T00:17:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free and Open Source Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.taucharts.com/\">TauCharts</a> - Unique syntax that lets the developer describe the data using DSL. Has the ability to create facets.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-02T00:17:24.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free and Open Source Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://dc-js.github.io/dc.js/\">dc.js</a> - D3 Library with <a href=\"http://square.github.io/crossfilter/\">crossfilter</a> support</li>","updatedAt":"2016-03-02T00:04:07.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free and Open Source Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.rgraph.net/\">rgraph</a> - 2D/3D javascript charts with google sheets import capabilites.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T23:55:01.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free and Open Source Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.chartjs.org/\">Chart.js</a> - Tiny library (11kb!) including core chart types.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free and Open Source Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://d3js.org/\">D3.js</a> - Allows the user to manipulate documents based on data to render charts in SVG.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free and Open Source Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/danvk/dygraphs\">dygraphs</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/danvk/dygraphs\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2995,\"repo\":\"danvk/dygraphs\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Interactive zoomable time series charts.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free and Open Source Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/palantir/plottable\">Plottable</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/palantir/plottable\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">2.9k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":2888,\"repo\":\"palantir/plottable\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Library with OOP style syntax to build charts.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Free Libraries</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://developers.google.com/chart/\">Google Charts</a> - Maps are dialed in (of course) and some cool animation options. Extensive docs and use community (forum).</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Framework-Specific Libraries</h2><h3>Angular</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/n3-charts/line-chart\">n3-charts</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/n3-charts/line-chart\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1208,\"repo\":\"n3-charts/line-chart\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Easy to use library written with AngularJS, rendering charts with D3.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Framework-Specific Libraries</h2><h3>Ember</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://addepar.github.io/ember-charts/#/overview\">Ember Charts</a> - Five basic chart types ready to go in Ember.js projects.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Framework-Specific Libraries</h2><h3>jQuery</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.flotcharts.org/\">Flot</a> - A JavaScript charting library for jQuery. Contains useful chart types but looks like it may no longer be in active development.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Framework-Specific Libraries</h2><h3>React</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/esbullington/react-d3\">react-d3</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/esbullington/react-d3\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">1.8k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":1762,\"repo\":\"esbullington/react-d3\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Charting library that relies on React for generating SVG markup and d3 to calculate path values.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Visualization Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://datavizcatalogue.com\">Dataviz Catalogue</a> - A place to go when you're wondering which chart type is best. A project by Severino Ribecca.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Visualization Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://stephanieevergreen.com\">Evergreen Data</a> - Information and opinions on presenting data more effectively.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Visualization Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://flowingdata.com\">Flowing Data</a> - A resource on maps, visualizations, stats, and design by Nathan Yau, formerly of the New York Times.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Visualization Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://junkcharts.typepad.com\">Junk Charts</a> - Dataviz critic (and Columbia professor) Kaiser Fung breaks down data visualizations to identify what is wrong and recommends ways to make them better.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Visualization Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://www.visualisingdata.com\">Visualizing Data</a> - Dataviz consultant Andy Kirk compiles examples, resources, and reference materials on the subject of charting and visualization.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"},{"categoryHTML":"<h2>Data Visualization Resources</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"http://well-formed-data.net/archives/1210/little-boxes\">Well Formed Data</a> - Thought pieces on information visualization and design by Moritz Stefaner previously of the World Economic Forum.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-02-19T22:15:45.000Z"}]},"previous":{"id":"awesomes/git